ning facilitated by trained counsellors. it provides an opportunity for women to meet together for peer support, within a supported environment.</li>		<li class="description">MRC also runs <em>group work for women</em> who have completed counselling but who wish to access further support. The group work is aimed specifically at developing confidence and looks at issues around body image and self assertiveness. The group also provides a social network for women who may be isolated and vulnerable.</li>		<li class="description">For information or advice on any of these services, please ring the MRC office on: 0161 273 4591 (Open Monday to Friday, 10am to 4pm)</li>		</ul>	</div> </div><div class="row">   <div class="col-1 col-sm-1 col-md-1 col-lg-1">&nbsp;</div>    <div class="col-11 col-sm-11 col-md-11 col-lg-11">  		<h3>Independent Sexual Violence Advisor (ISVA)</h3>
